SIMPLE: semidouble
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Semidouble
<hw>Sem"i*dou`ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld>
<def>An office or feast celebrated with less solemnity than the double
ones. See <er>Double</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 8.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semidouble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Semidouble
<hw>Sem`i*dou"ble</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the
outermost stamens converted into petals, while the inner ones remain
perfect; -- said of a flower.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semifable</ent>⟦br⟧
